summary:
Qiuling is Partner at EY (Ernst & Young), based in Amsterdam. She is experienced in serving large international clients in the wealth & asset management and banking industry. As the EY FSO NL Digital Innovation Leader from 2018, she has transformed audits to be more and more data driven and automated.

Next to client serving work, she is passionate on coaching people and supported the management team in the area of “people”. This varies from mentorship, recruitment, setting HR policies including inclusiveness, to being part of the appraisal committee. Through this experience, she has been appointed in 2022 as the Talent Leader of the EY Financial Services in the Netherlands covering approximately 1000 FTEs.

Qiuling also has been seconded to EY Shanghai, China during November 2011 and October 2013. Through her prominent role in numerous audit clients and projects in the Netherlands, she was able to leverage her experience and knowledge from the mature markets and given the opportunity to use this in growing markets like China at that time. During her time in China, she served in particularly private equity and banking clients in Shanghai and Beijing.
